\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would he ever get up in the night if they cried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes, yes, he'd get up in the night, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And would he ever take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes, I'd wash them on Sunday morning - he'd off to the park. Off to the park in a pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you know what your husband earned then before 1919?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, I did know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How much of that would he give to you - how much did he earn - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well - his - he was only - if he worked a week or a fortnight he'd be out two or three weeks so really we didn't know - I couldn't say - his wages were two pound. Two pound - if he worked a full week. And he was a boilermaker. A trade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3540316\charrsid2041182 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 man. No, he was a trade - yes. And I - he got - he got two pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How much of that would he give you when he was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Thirty-five shillings, yes. And keep the five. And he'd have union money and all - to pay out of that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you discuss with your husband how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You just sort of knew what you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, we pulled both together sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How many rooms were there in Bickerton Street first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 It was one floor you had was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No - upstairs. Upstairs. And two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 A back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 That was included in the two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, you see like a four bedroomed - four roomed house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And outside toilet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And what about Twist Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Oh we had - three bedrooms there. A sitting room - of course they didn't call 'em sitting rooms when - those days, they called 'em parlours. They do in this street now, call 'em parlours. There was a sitting room, kitchen, back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And still an outside toilet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were there any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 With my - when my - my husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. No, nobody at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you pay anyone to help you in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Cash was too short for you to do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh - took me all me time to pay me way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, no, had a dolly tub and legs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were the clothes made or mended by you or your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. I - used to do all the mending, I can't make. But I did all the mending - I darned and that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 I like knitting but I can't sew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh I can't even do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were they always new when you bought clothes either for yourself or the children or were they sometimes second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3540316\charrsid2041182  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3540316\charrsid2041182  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
hand more or less, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 For yourself as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And what about shoes for yourself and the children - would these have been new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well that - periodical we might get a pair for four and eleven you know - they were only four and eleven those a pair - I think the price of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would you say that you would mainly have had second hand things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes. Oh yes. yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your husband help with jobs in the house - did he help with cleaning and cooking and the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh - he'd perhaps dust or clean the windows for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did he do the fires for you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 If I - I - sometimes when he'd come in of a morning hadn't been working if the fire wasn't - he'd clear the fire for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did he do any decorating or repairs or improvements to the home in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 But he would have helped dress and undress the children would he as they got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Oh yes, yes. Mind you, he only was - I only had him eleven years you know. Just a short time that was all as he had so you couldn't expect - I've had to be mother - and father to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You've made a good job of it by the way they've turned out haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well everybody tells me that. And they've brought me no - no disgrace. No. Only just losing - rearing them. 'Course with - everybody doesn't know in this world what - what they've got to feel. I always think
 to myself well it's terrible to think - I've worked hard to bring them up and then they taken the - they tell me there's a purpose but I can't see it. Yes. Well, yes I suppose it is really. Yes. Well I won't mind if I thought I was going - be un - yes - 
and more particular with the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You felt close to them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well - I mean - I've had them such a long time you understand. And the eldest boy lived at home with me and he was just like a husband. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your children have regular household tasks to help you in the house when they got a little older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well they - this oldest girl of mine was working when she was fourteen. She left school when she was fourteen. She went - went to work in Sefton General. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What time would you have put your children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
In the - winter months they went to bed between seven and eight at night. And in the summer months they went to bed about - round about eight. When it was a bit lighter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When would they have put themselves to bed or would you always have put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well I've always - been a worrier you know. You know, knowing that - I would never go out and leave them. I've never - been out and left them at all. I think May was twelve when I started to go out - I thought 
well she's getting old enough - a friend of mine said, well come on - go out and have a - a tour or two with me. May's getting old enough now to - to be able to give yourself a break. And that was when I started to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 So they put themselves to bed at about that age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 I'd - tell them what to do and then - she would put them to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 But normally up to that time you would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Up to that time - I never bothered going out at all. No. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What sleeping arrangements did you have for the children - did they share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, they both had their own bedrooms, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 This was when you only had two when you were in Twist Street - you had four children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How would the sleeping arrangements have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well the two boys slept in the little bedroom and - Brenda slept in the middle bedroom and May and I had the front - the other - other room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What room did you use for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I had to bath them downstairs. Front of the fire, yes
. In the dolly tub sometimes. You see, you see them there and their heads sticking over the dolly tub - well we had no alternative did we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When would you have bathed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well they washed every night. From - top to bottom. And bathed - on Satur
day night. This was a regular routine. And a - a couple of teaspoonfuls of - oh what do you call it, to open their bowels, you get a big bottle for fourpence those days - syrup of figs. Oh they'd be round the bath you know with their mouths open. People w
o
uld tell you know if they were here - I'd love one of them to be here. Oh I would. They'd have been in tucks listening to it. But they can remember you know, all standing round - I used to send them to the one shop in Park Road and they'd get a bottle lik
e that - loose - syrup of figs. Yes. Oh it cleared them out didn't it. They could take more than I could because I couldn't have taken it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When did they have clean clothes - would they have had them on the Saturday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh you mean underclothes? Oh 
once a week. They all were stripped on a Saturday night and washed and many a time every night used to have to take their stockings off and wash them for - clean for next morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Where were the meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 In the - in the living room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 That's the back room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well - the kitchen. Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were there any occasions when meals were eaten in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, we all lived in the kitchen - all had meals in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Where did you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 In the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What did you cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes, I had a gas stove those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 In the kitchen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What time in the morning would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh half past eight to nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What members of the family were present - would your husband have had breakfast with you or would he have gone out before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh he'd have gone out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What did you usually give them for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well there's no cornflakes. Had to have bread and jam or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Bread and milk and tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What would they have had for their midday meals - what would have been typical midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well - pan of scouse or spice balls. You go to barrows, you know, get a - big jug of gravy and what 
have you. You'd make a pan of scouse or something you know. Make a good dinner. Or put it in the pan and mash boiled - pan of potatoes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh I had a joint on a Sunday. Little but of a joint, yes, on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about Sunday breakfast - would that be any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well we'd have - perhaps a bit of fried bacon and tomatoes- yes - just to make a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about your evening meals - what would you have had?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When they were all small you mean? Yes. W
ell we'd have - tin of fruit or something like that with custard with it you know. Sunday was always a special - special day. Yes, something different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What would you have had in the week for your evening meal - would you have had tea with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would you have had a cooked meal or just an ordinary bread and butter meal at tea time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I mean if there was coned beef or - you'd get corned beef those days for fourpence a pound, you know, fourpence a pound. What is it - i
t's more than that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you make your own bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Or any jam, pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Not when they were little. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you grow your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you keep any hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How many times a week did you eat meat when you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Oh - when my husband was with me - you mean with my husband - oh we'd have something - meat each night for him - oh coming in. Oh yes, we'd have something - liver and 
bacon or sausages or something like that. Some sort - or potato pie or you know, some little thing for - steak and kidney pie or something like that when he come in. Something - something to liven him up when he came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you ever obtain extra meat from poaching - any rabbits from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you ever go short so that your husband and children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well - no, I wouldn't say we went short - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your husband need to have larger helpings of food than you or the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I always gave him a bit more. Oh yes, I always felt a man wanted more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were your children allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes, we never stopped them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Could they - choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well they'd take what was cooked and - either take it or leave it sort of thing, yes. Yes, if they didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What would you say if they left some food uneaten on their plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 I'd tell 'em I'd - make them eat it when they come in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And you would do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did they have to wait until things were passed to them like the salt or were they able to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh they'd ask for it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 If it was there they got it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were they encouraged to hold their knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes. I've caught mine you know doing this business with their knives and forks when I've been outside and it's got on me nerves you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 So you corrected them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Recalling when you were a child you said you had to find out the hard way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, I did. No, I - I made them do as they were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you allowe them to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, no books. I wouldn't let them read at the table. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When did members of the family leave the table - were they allowed to leave before everybody else had finished or did they have to wait?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh no, they'd go away when they wanted to. Yes, when they finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did all the family sit at the one table for the meal - did they have regular places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your husband always have his own seat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And you have yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes. We all - always had our own places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
How would you have served the meal - would you have served straight from the sacusepan onto the plates or would you have put things into serving dishes and put it on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, I'd serve them from the stove outside and bring the plates in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How would you have fed the children when they were too young to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I fed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 On your knee or on a chair or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No - chairs. Never seen a chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Never saw a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What did you used to do - tie them in an ordinary chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
No, I'd sit 'em on me knee. Yes, and I'd have the - yes, I'd have it here you see. I'd feed them first. I'd feed them - they'd have their meals first. And then I'd have mine after. Many times was cold as you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How old would the children have been when they joined in family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh when they started going to school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Up til then they would sit on your knee mainly would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Main - mainly on my knee yes. Oh I think they're lovely 'til - oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
When your children were young did you feel there was a right and a wrong way of bringing up children - did you husband and you have the same ideas about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were you conscious of the right and wrong way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you talk about this with your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I mean - do you mean - bringing - manners and all that sort of business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you discuss this sort of thing with your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 We
ll not really because I mean - as I said we weren't - we didn't have that long together sort of thing. I mean they were only small when he died you know. May was only eight when he died. She was the eldest of the four. So - we hadn't much time together, h
ad we, to discuss anything. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, I had to work - had to do it all myself. Cope with everything myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Was your mother alive when your children were small - did you see anything of your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, oh me mother used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How often would you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh practically every morning she'd call in. Oh yes, she'd come -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You saw more of her then than you did before you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Than I did when - when I was a child. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Do you know if you and she had the same ideas on this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. Her ideas were different than mine. Very very different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 We
ll my mother - was a woman like this. She thought she'd had it hard and I suppose she thought well we should have it hard, you understand but I always said if I had it hard and I had - was bringing my children up I never let 'em - I hoped they wouldn't ge
t as hard life as I had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 She really made you feel that you wouldn't want anybody to go through what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Anybody else - I wouldn't like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 But your mother felt if she had it hard you jolly well were going to have the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes. And
 she lived for today my mother did. Oh yes. Never thought about tomorrow - she lived for today. She'd tell you that too you know, me mother would
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 It's the way she was made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about your mother-in-law - did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh she only lived - four or five doors from me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would she come in and see you quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh she'd come in - very often to see me. But that was all as I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would you ever ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Do you think you and she had roughly the same ideas or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
No, I think mam had a - a better bringing up really. But she - than my mother, yes. But of course she was - had thirteen children of her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children - did you feel that affection was necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh I give 'em all the affection 'cos I loved them. Oh I loved them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about safety and food and discipline - were you anxious for their safety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh
 I'd worry st - I used to worry stiff if they weren't in for time, you know, I'd be at the door to see were they all right. They were on me mind the whole time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about food - were you conscious f the right and the wrong food for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You mean when they were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When they were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, oh when they were small, yes. Well I'd give them what I - what me purse could afford to manage to buy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you believe in discipline for your children - did you give them a lot of discipline or not use much towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
No, not really. I'd make them come in and go out and do - what I - and come in to time you know. And if I told 'em - their tea and all that was on - well you know, their meal, I'd expect them to come in - went to sc
hool I'd expect them to come back again to have it at the proper time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you want them to share their worries with you - did you feel they did and did you want them to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well if - they were in any - they didn't - were never in trouble. They never were in trouble my - any of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 The little worries that children have - would they have shared them with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh I think so. Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I expected them to give me the same respect as I gave them. And they have done ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When the children were young did you ever manage to leave them so you could go out when you and your husband were newly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 We never went out. No. Never went out at all - we never went over
 the door. We had one week - I think at Morton and he came for the weekend on the Saturday and went home on the Sunday and then I broke me heart. Being parted from him. And that's the only holiday we've ever had in the short }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182  life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And he only had a weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 He had the weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Not really, I mean, more or less, I mean, if there was grown ups they'd go out and play you know, they wouldn't - I wouldn't want them, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
You mean - as regards - going out. Well I used - when they went out and went to school or anything I used to tell 'em not to - talk to strangers or not to take money off strange people or sweets or anything like that. Used to always tell 'em refuse it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What sort of characteristics would you say were important - that you'd want them to have when they grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I mean - Brenda wanted to be a nurse. And of course - May of course
 was the eldest - she went as a - just said, she went into Sefton General. She was in the laundry there. And of course Jack was in an office - he left school at fourteen. And Ernie - he went into the Co-op. He was a rounds-man for the Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you tell your children to hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes I did. Yes. I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well - I would always tell 'em to pick their company, who they did play with. I
t's not the children really - it's the company that they get in - the background.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Was it because the parents didn't care - is this why you wouldn't have found a child suitable for your own children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well you - really I think it was more or less,
 you know, they were a bit on - more on the rough side and I didn't want my children - you know, to join in with them -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would you have said to them I don't want you to play with so and so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 I used to say I'll be - bring him here or here here again, you don't go out, sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen to them - would you punish them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I wouldn't hit them but I'd just give them a good - dressing down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You would never hit them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. I don't ever remember - no, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Do you remember any particular occasion when you punished them - what sort of things would they have to have done for you really to tell them off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well - I've never ever remember giving 'em a good hid
ing, you know. No, no, I've never ever - I've hurt me own hands you know clouting them across the legs. Always remember one of our neighbours saying - hit them on their b.t. and you'll break no bones. But I - do you know, I couldn't give them a hiding.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both of you or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I must say - the four of them give me every respect they could possibly do - give me
 and I've never known them to answer me back. Whatever they've had in their mind or thought if they've been getting a telling off I - they've never answered - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You influenced them more than your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 For the simple fact that the eldest child was eight when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When he died, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You worked after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182  but you didn't work until you were a widow did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When you were working you said the children got themselves off in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And you'd get the breakfast ready?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, all ready for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Some people think that children should be with their mother all the time, others think it is not necessary and does them good to be with other people quite a lot - 
what did you think about that? Do you think it important for the mother to be with the children all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes I do. I do. I do. I don't think there would be half of the crimes and what have you today - if they had their mother's was at home and g
ive 'em a little bit more love. To make them feel they care and I think they would give 'em more respect. I do honest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 A - a few cakes and a tine of fruit, you know, make a little bit of a special effort for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Would they have a present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Not really - I couldn't afford it, no, couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Can you remember anything you did with your husband and your eldest child on a Christmas Day - what sort of r
outine would you have had on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
Well, I mean - as regards - celebrating you mean? Well I mean - he was out of work such a lot at Christmas. So really was - money's been tight, ever so - always. No good us saying that it was because it's a
lways been tight. And it's only - I've only had like since the children have been grown up that I've felt any - any benefit of it. And you see, when I was feeling the benefit they were - the boys were - taken from me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Never mind, there's got to be a reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 
No, we made their own musical instruments. Out of a comb or something like that. As long a - you know, you could see the men with the tin whistle. They brought those sort of things in. Drove me up the wall very nearly with those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you play games with the children yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Only ludo or - oh yes, or cards or whatever - snakes and ladders and all sorts of things, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your husband join in the games or play different ones with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh he would. Oh he played with them, yes, I can't say he - he wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were there any books, newspapers or magazines in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh they'd buy the - you mean as regards Beano's and all like - books - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you read at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, only the Echo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your husband read books at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, only the - the morning papers and the evening papers that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Didn't belong to a Library then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you ever read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh - occasionally if they had odd books they'd read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you take the children out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. Nobody wanted us with four of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were they taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh I've took them shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Mainly with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 With - always with me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did the children ever go out with just their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Only on a Sunday morning as I said, yes. Just for the walk, yes, and dressed up. You know in all their foll-de-rolls going to the park.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What did you do on any Bank Holidays with your husband and children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Went to the park - round the lake there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You had that one holiday in your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738008 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182  life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And your husband just joined you for the weekend?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Just for the weekend. And I wished I'd never gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 How did you spend Saturdays in those days? Were they any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, he'd be off to the football match you know. It was only fourpence to go then. And enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 What about Sundays - did you or the children put on different clothes on the Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well only our clean ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 They wouldn't be Sunday clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well the children'd have their Sunday ones on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 But you wouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh no. Mind you, I always kept myself clean and tidy always. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on a Sunday or did you think it did not matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Well I think myself Sunday should be kept as Sunday. Yes, I feel that. I did do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you allow your children to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, I never let them run - run the streets on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. Only christenings or anything like that, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you belong to a choir or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did the church that you did go to occasionally run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You didn't belong to any other clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did your children go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did they go to any adult or family services at the church or just Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No, only Sunday school. They left school you know when they were fourteen. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were your children taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Oh going to bed. Yes, always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 And you would have taught them this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes, I - no I taught, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Yes. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 You were very conscious that the Labour party was the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Very - I'm very conscious now too and I'm seventy-eight - seventy-nine very near.
