e did - he was a strong Conservative. But he changed his views. I always remember him saying when - lady opposite said, Ernie Griffiths, I'm surprised at you. You turn coat. Miss Jones, he said, I'm like the kittens. I've got my eyes open. And I thought i
t was a jolly good - no, I thought it was a jolly - good answer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Nobody's business except your own anyway is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Your own - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Were you a member of a political party at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid283337 MG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15211515 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5471496\charrsid2041182 Did you ever do any work for the political parties?
